# lp-history-reconstructor

Uniswap V2 LP event sourcing: eth_getLogs backfill → Parquet → fold Sync → verify getReserves().

## Python style

- Python 3.12, type hints on public signatures, functions over classes.
- Short docstrings that explain the "why".
- Lint: `uv run ruff check .` must pass before any commit.
- English only in comments, logs, and docs.

## Mandatory patterns

- New parameter → YAML in `config/` + pydantic in `settings.py`. Never hardcode.
- Secrets (`LP_ETH_RPC_URL`) only via env / `.env`, never YAML.
- Always write events through the Parquet loader; persist checkpoints after each chunk.
- Business metrics (IL, fees, PnL) belong in later dbt phases — not in Python fold logic yet.

## Tests

- Mock RPC with respx; fixtures under `tests/fixtures/`.
- Run with `uv run pytest`.
